05/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria's President Georgi Parvanov on Friday (3 September) called for stepping up reforms in the security sector and tightening anti-terrorism measures in the country.
His comments followed the tragic developments in southern Russia.
Parvanov stressed the need for better preparedness in order to meet the ongoing international threat of terrorism, as well as the importance of fighting organised crime in the region.
(Sega - 04/09/04;
bTV, Darik - 03/09/04)
